<!-- FAQ -->
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq supporting-questions">
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Can I use mouth tape on an airplane?</h3><p>Yes — it works great for flights. The dry cabin air makes mouth breathing worse, leading to sore throat and dehydration. Mouth tape keeps you nasal breathing for the duration of the flight. Just apply it after takeoff when you're ready to sleep.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How long does the white noise machine battery last for travel?</h3><p>6-8 hours on a full charge, depending on volume. That covers a full night in a hotel. It also charges via USB-C, so you can top it up with any travel charger or laptop.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>Will TSA allow these items in carry-on?</h3><p>Yes — all three items are TSA-friendly. The white noise machine has a small lithium battery (allowed), the sleep mask has a small Bluetooth battery (allowed), and the mouth tape is just adhesive strips. No issues at security.</p></div>
  <div class="faq-item"><h3>How does this compare to the Deep Sleep Bundle?</h3><p>The Travel Sleep Kit is optimized for portability — it swaps the sleep spray (which can leak in luggage) for mouth tape (travel-friendly). The Deep Sleep Bundle is better for a permanent home setup.</p></div>
